-- CLS Bank Says Currency-Trading Settlement Value Rose in February
-- B y   D a v i d   G o o d m a n
-- 2012-03-06T10:14:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/cls-bank-says-currency-trading-settlement-value-rose-in-february.html
CLS Bank, the New York-based
operator of the largest currency-trading settlement system, said
it handled an average $4.68 trillion of trades a day last month,
up from $4.24 trillion in January.  CLS said it settled an average 724,132 trading instructions
per day in February, from 654,914 a month earlier, according to
an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
